page.title: 08E. CHARMINSTER - WILDLIFE 2
page.content:
Those interested in birds and butterflies will find much to interest them in this section of the parish. No comprehensive survey has been carried out, but casual walkers have observed the following in an afternoon:
BIRDS All the more common wild birds were spotted, but notable{sightings} included heron, owl, buzzard, hawk and yellow hammers.
BUTTERFLIES The many wild flowers and varied hedgerows attracted: Meadow Brown Orange Tip Small Copper Marbled White Common Blue Red Admiral Plain White Green Streak Speckled Brown Tortoiseshell
